  "prompt": "What are some of the best stories about Virender Sehwag?",
  "response": "Virender Sehwag, the former Indian cricketer, is known not only for his explosive batting but also for his humorous and witty nature. Here are some of the best stories about him:\n\n1. **The \"I Played Like Sachin\" Incident:**\n   During the 2001 Border-Gavaskar Trophy in India, Sehwag scored a brilliant century in Chennai. When asked about his performance in the post-match presentation, he famously said, \"I was just trying to play like Sachin [Tendulkar].\" The response became a legendary quote and showcased his humility and admiration for his teammate.\n\n2. **The \"500 Runs\" Misunderstanding:**\n   In 2008, during a Test match against Australia in Adelaide, Sehwag was batting at 293 when a fan shouted, \"Sehwag, 500 runs today!\" Misunderstanding the fan's enthusiasm, Sehwag replied, \"Why not? I'll try.\" Although he didn't score 500, he did go on to make a memorable 319, which was then the highest individual score by an Indian in Test cricket.\n\n3. **The 'Multan ka Sultan' Title:**\n   After scoring a double century in the first Test against Pakistan in Multan in 2004, Sehwag was bestowed with the title 'Multan ka Sultan' (The Sultan of Multan). He celebrated his achievement by wearing a traditional Pakistani cap in the dressing room and jokingly called himself the 'Sultan' among his teammates.\n\n4. **His Epic Reaction to Sreesanth's Over:**\n   During a Test match against South Africa in 2006, Sreesanth bowled an over that went for 25 runs. When he came back to the dressing room, Sehwag, in his characteristic blunt humor, said, \"Sreesanth, you have made history today. No one has ever conceded 25 runs in an over in Test cricket!\" Sreesanth, who was already down, burst into laughter at Sehwag's comment.\n\n5. **The 'Forgotten Birthday' Story:**\n   Once, Sehwag's wife, Aarti, jokingly told him that he had forgotten his own birthday. Sehwag, with his usual wit, replied, \"No, I didn't forget. I was just waiting for someone to remind me so that I could celebrate!\"\n\n6. **The Hilarious Sledging Incident with Shoaib Akhtar:**\n   During a match against Pakistan, Shoaib Akhtar tried to sledge Sehwag by saying, \"Viru, tu kuch nahin kar sakta (Viru, you can't do anything).\" Sehwag, without missing a beat, replied, \"Shoaib, tu bhi toh kuch nahin kar sakta. Mere saath toh tujhe match fix karna padega (Shoaib, you can't do anything either. You'll have to fix the match to get me out).\"\n\nThese anecdotes highlight not just Sehwag's incredible talent on the field but also his fun-loving and down-to-earth personality off it.",
